@REM==============================================================================

@node "CLOSE_BUTTON" "Main Window: Close Button"
@prev "MAIN_WINDOW"

                              @{u}CLOSE BUTTON:@{uu}

 The close button has a double-function. When pressing only once, all
 currently empty nodes (@{"Status" link "ACTION_FIELD" 0} Awaiting Call) get made inactive
 (Node Offhook). When all nodes are Offhook and you press the close
 button again, the Server closes and FAME terminates. The state of the nodes
 after closing them depends on the settings in @{fg fill}SystemEditor/Node Edit/More
 NodeEdit/Default OffHook.@{fg text}

 If you have started the Server in @{"IDLE" link "TOOLTYPES" 0} mode, it will terminate after the
 first click on the close button, because no nodes are started and therefor
 it's not necessary to shutdown them first.

 @{b}NOTE:@{ub} It's not possible to terminate FAME until all nodes are free !

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "NODE_SWITCH" "Main Window: Node Cycling"

                              @{u}NODE-CYCLING:@{uu}

 If your BBS has more nodes than the Server is able to display at one time,
 the nodes gets split to fit on your screen. In this case you are able
 to choose which nodes the Server should display by pressing on this Gadget
 and choosing the node-range you would like to see now.

 If all of your nodes fit on screen, this Gadget is disabled (ghosted) and
 can't be used.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT" "Main Window: About Button"
@next "SAVE_WIN"

                              @{u}ABOUT BUTTON:@{uu}

 By clicking on this button you'll get another window containing information
 about all guys who helped in the creation of FAME. The following buttons
 are available inside the About Window:


 @{"  Quit About  " link "ABOUT_QUIT" 0}@{"  Main Code  " link "ABOUT_MAIN_CODE" 0}@{" Develop Team " link "ABOUT_DEVELOP_TEAM" 0}@{" Support Team " link "ABOUT_SUPPORT_TEAM" 0}@{" Support BBS  " link "ABOUT_SUPPORT_BBS" 0}
 @{" Beta Testers " link "ABOUT_BETA_TESTERS" 0}@{" Dist. Sites " link "ABOUT_DIST_SITES" 0}@{" ------------ " link "UNUSED" 0}@{" ------------ " link "UNUSED" 0}@{" ------------ " link "UNUSED" 0}


 Also your Registration number, the SysOp- and BBS-Name are shown inside
 the About window if you have started at least one Node.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_QUIT" "About Window: Quit About Button"
@prev "ABOUT"

                        @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: QUIT ABOUT@{uu}

 Press this button or the window close button to get rid of the about
 window.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_MAIN_CODE" "About Window: Main Code Button"
@prev "ABOUT"

                        @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: MAIN CODE@{uu}

 Lists the main programmers of the FAME System incl. their E-Mail adresses.
 These persons are the Inventors of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_DEVELOP_TEAM" "About Window: Develop Team Button"
@prev "ABOUT"

                         @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: DEVELOP TEAM@{uu}

 Lists the FAME development team and their E-Mail adresses. These guys are
 responsible for external FAME-Programs like FullEditor, User-Editor or the
 FAMEChat. Also they are developing the Programmer-Examples and some of the
 documents including the Installation-Script.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_SUPPORT_TEAM" "About Window: Support Team Button"
@prev "ABOUT"

                         @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: SUPPORT TEAM@{uu}

 Lists the people and their E-Mail adresses who are developing FAME-Tools 
 and other things related to FAME, mainly BBS-Doors for the FAME Doorport.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_SUPPORT_BBS" "About Window: Support BBS Button"
@prev "ABOUT"

                        @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: SUPPORT BBS@{uu}

 Here you have the phone numbers to call the Support BBS for FAME. This BBS
 offers the full support for FAME including the latest updates of FAME,
 their external Doors and also all doors from the @{"Supporter Team" link "ABOUT_SUPPORT_TEAM" 0}.

 If you have suggestions or bug-reports for FAME or any of their external
 tools, please write these reports also in this BBS, as all reports are
 stored there and forwarded immediatly to the @{"Coders" link "ABOUT_DEVELOP_TEAM" 0} of the FAME-System.

 Additionally it's also possible to write your Suggestions via E-Mail, but
 we recommend to call this BBS first, as this Board will be called every 
 day by the coders.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_BETA_TESTERS" "About Window: Beta Testers Button"
@prev "ABOUT"

                        @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: BETA TESTERS@{uu}

 Here you have a list of all the guys who are testing the FAME-System.
 These guys have the hard work to find all the nasty bugs and other things a
 coder misses...

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ABOUT_DIST_SITES" "About Window: Dist. Sites Button"

                         @{u}ABOUT WINDOW: DIST. SITES@{uu}

 Lists all the BBS-Systems where you can get the FAME-System as a registered
 User, but in difference to the @{"Support-BBS" link "ABOUT_SUPPORT_BBS" 0} you only get working versions
 of FAME and their required external programs, Beta-Versions are only
 accessable on the  Support BBS !

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SAVE_WIN" "Main Window: Save Window Position"

                            @{u}SAVE WIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button allows you to save the position of the Server Window without
 entering the coordinates in the @{fg fill}SystemEditor@{fg text} under @{fg fill}Server Settings@{fg text}. Simply
 move the window to the position where the Server should open it's window
 everytime and click on the @{b}Save Win@{ub} button. The coordinates of the window
 are now copied to the Server Settings and The Server will open it's window
 at exactly the same position next time.

 The server also saves the positions of the @{"small/big" link "WIN_SIZE" 0} Serverwindow and the
 position of the @{"Spy Window" link "SPY_NODE" 0}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ICONIFY" "Main Window: Iconify Button"

                             @{u}ICONIFY BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button allows you to iconify the Server. When pressed, the icon from
 the Server is used as an AppIcon, which will be shown on the Workbench
 screen. If you want to use another icon for iconifying the server, simply
 create/copy the icon of your choice to @{fg shine}Env:Sys/def_FAME.info@{fg text} and the
 Server will use this icon to iconify the Server.

 To start the Server in Iconify mode, you'll have to use the @{"ToolTypes" link "CONFIGURATION" 0} or
 set the @{fg fill}Iconify option@{fg text} in the @{fg fill}SystemEditor/Server Settings@{fg text}.
 Also you could set here the X and Y coordinates for the AppIcon to let it
 appear on the same place everytime the Server gets iconified. Enter the 
 Pixel-coordinates for the AppIcon.

 More Informations about the Server Settings are available in the System-
 Editor documentation.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "PORTLIST" "Main Window: Ports/Processes/Handler Button"

                     @{u}PORTS/PROCESSES/HANDLER BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button opens another window with definitions to auto-start external
 programs on specific actions by FAME. So you could i.e. let the Server
 execute every day at a specific time a User-Lister, which creates bulls
 for all your users. So this (in most cases very time-intensive) actions
 have to be executed only once, not for every user.


               @{fg shine}<FUNCTION IS CURRENTLY NOT IMPLEMENTED!>@{fg text}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "WIN_SIZE" "Main Window: Resize Server-Window"

                           @{u}^ (RESIZE) BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button enables/disables the button bank at the bottom of the
 Serverwindow. In some cases it could be useful to display only the nodes
 and not the button banks too, i.e. if your Workbench screen is full of
 windows or you need a short overview of what happend on your BBS. To do
 this, simply press this button and the whole button bank disappears.
 Another click on this button lets the button bank appear again.

 To save the actual Server window setting, use the @{"SAVE WIN" link "SAVE_WIN" 0} button.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "NODES" "Main Window: Node Buttons"

                           @{u}NODE <X> BUTTON(S):@{uu}

 Depending on the number of nodes your BBS has, you'll see the according
 Node @{fg fill}<X>@{fg text} buttons, where @{fg fill}<X>@{fg text} stands for the nodenumbers ranging from 0 to
 your maximum number of nodes, i.e. if your BBS has three nodes, you'll 
 have the Node-Buttons @{b}NODE 0@{ub} , @{b}NODE 1@{ub} and @{b}NODE 2@{ub} displayed in the Server
 window as shown in the @{"Server Main Window" link "MAIN_WINDOW" 0} description.

 By clicking on one of these Node buttons the according Node screen opens,
 or, if it is already open it will pop to the front.
 If no user is online, you'll see the start screen of FAME, which is
 described in the @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} documentation. If a user is online, you are now
 able to view/edit his actions. Please note that scrolling is much slower
 if the node screen is open, so if you don't need the screen, you should 
 leave it closed for speed reasons.

 If you click on one of the node buttons and no screen appears, it is
 possible that something is wrong with the communication of the Server and
 the according node. In this case, the Server performs a ScreenBeep after
 ten seconds of unsuccessful communication to inform you about the problem.
 If this happens, try to restart FAME or consult the FAQ in the FAME main
 documentation.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "CHAT_SWITCH" "Main Window: Chat on/off"

                             @{u}CHATFLAG ON/OFF:@{uu}

 This flag determines if you want to be pageable by the '@{fg shine}O@{fg text}' command for the
 specific node. If set to on (checkmark appears) the users on this node are
 able to page you. If set to off, the users can't page you.

 @{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you use a replacement for the '@{fg shine}O@{fg text}' command, the replacement door
       is responsible for the checking of the ChatFlag!

 This flag is also setable in the @{fg fill}SystemEditor@{fg text} under @{fg fill}Node Edit@{fg text} Settings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ACTION_FIELD" "Main Window: Information Fields"

                        @{u}SERVER NODE-STATUS DISPLAY:@{uu}

 This field is used by the Server to display certain informations about
 the current status of the specific node. The field is seperated in four
 columns which shows the following informations:

   Actual User  @{b}->@{ub}  Name of the current online user, empty if node was
                    just started and no user is online yet.

      Location  @{b}->@{ub}  Location/Group of the current online user, empty if node
                    was just started and no user was online yet.

        Action  @{b}->@{ub}  Shows the node status or the user's current action.
                    Also if programs write to the server's action field,
                    those texts are displayed here.

      Baud/CPS  @{b}->@{ub}  Shows the current Baudrate. If no user is online, the
                    Initialization Baudrate of the node is shown, otherwise
                    the Baudrate of the online user will be displayed. When
                    a transfer is in progress, you'll see the UL/DL CPS rate
                    the user currently has.

 In addition, the whole line can be written in different colors to indicate
 special actions of the online user. The following colorcodes are available:

         Black  @{b}->@{ub}  Normal Textoutput, no special action.

          @{fg fill}Blue@{fg text}  @{b}->@{ub}  User is Hidden from other users. If another user takes a
                    look at the nodes by using the @{b}WHO@{ub} command, hidden
                    users are shown with the Name @{b}HIDDEN@{ub} and the Action
                    @{b}DO NOT DISTURB@{ub}. Additional informations could be found
                    in the @{"SystemEditor" link "SystemEditor.guide/Main"} documentation under the chapter
                    Access/Secure.

         @{fg shine}White@{fg text}  @{b}->@{ub}  The user has paged you. This color overwrites the Blue
                    colorcode in any case, so you are able to see which user
                    wants to chat with you. If you go to the SysOp chat with
                    a user who has paged you, the color will be restored
                    to the original state. If you have set the Page Flag off
                    and a user pages you, the action field of this user will
                    be written in white too.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "INFO" "Main Window: Info Button"

                               @{u}INFO BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button is used to start an external program which displays information
 about the current online user. As this program is an external program, you
 could easily replace it with your own program. 

 To let this work you must set the correct path to the Info program in the
 @{fg fill}SystemEditor@{fg text} under @{fg fill}FAME Modules@{fg text} (FAME-Info).

 @{b}NOTE:@{ub} If you plan to write your own program, make sure that you have the
       necessary know-how to write such kind of programs, or major problems
       may occure if you make mistakes when writing such programs! Take a
       look at the Programmer-documentation for further informations!


   @{fg shine}<THIS FUNCTION IS CURRENTLY UNDER DEVELOPMENT AND DOESN'T WORK YET!>@{fg text}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "NODE_USEREDIT" "Main Window: Start UserEditor to edit online User"

                          @{u}USER-EDITOR ON NODES:@{uu}

 If you want to edit the settings of an online user, click on this button.
 This requires that you have set the correct path to the external
 User-Editor in the @{fg fill}SystemEditor@{fg text} under @{fg fill}FAME Modules@{fg text}. If you click on this
 button, the User-Editor will be started with two arguments given, so if you
 want to write your own one, you must support the following template:

                        @{fg shine}FAME-LOCATION/A, SLOT/N@{fg text}

 So the Server may call the User-Editor in the following way:

                          @{fg shine}User-Editor FAME: 10@{fg text}

 This will force the User-Editor to load in the Settings from @{fg shine}FAME:Settings/@{fg text}
 and also immediatly load in the Usersettings for SlotNumber @{fg shine}10@{fg text}.

 If a user is shown in the @{"Status-Display" link "ACTION_FIELD" 0} of the Server but is no longer
 online, you could also use this button to edit his settings! The Server
 sends the Userslot argument the Slotnumber of the user which was last
 online.

 @{b}WARNING:@{ub} If you change the settings of an online user and save them, the
          changes you've made will be overwritten when the user logs out!!
          FAME copies the user.datas of the online user out of the normal
          user.data and uses the temporary datas for the time the user is
          online. If you make any changes on the online user, these changes
          will only be saved in the real user.datas! When the user logs out,
          FAME copies the temporary datas back into the real user.datas and
          overwrites your changes. For security reasons it's not allowed
          for the User-Editor to edit the temporary datas, as this
          could cause trouble if the user edits his datas at the same time!
          We are working on a way to make this possible, but this may take
          some time until it's finished.
          @{fg shine}So please *DON'T* change user.datas of an online user, only change
          Datas of users which are no longer online until we have found a
          solution!@{fg text}

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SYSOPLOGIN" "Main Window: Sysop Login Button"

                            @{u}SYSOP LOGIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button lets you login as SysOp with the full login procedure. You 
 will not asked be for a Username/Password in this Login mode. After
 pressing this button select the node you wish to login on as SysOp. Click
 on the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = nodenr. you wish) and FAME starts the Login
 procedure. It's not necessary to have the node screen open, the login
 will be done in any case.

 This function is equal to the @{fg shine}<F1>@{fg text} key in the Node Startup-Screen of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "LOCALLOGIN" "Main Window: Local Login Button"

                          @{u}LOCAL LOGIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button allows you to login local under a specific Username. Of course
 you will not be asked for a Password as this Check is disabled when login
 is from the local side. 
 After pressing this button click on the node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you 
 wish to login on (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = the nodenr. you wish).

 The fact that you now have to enter the username that you wish to login as
 means that you need to open the node screen to type the details into.

 Of course you could also login using the @{"Spy Mode" link "SPY_NODE" 0}, if you wish.

 This function is equal to the @{fg shine}<F2>@{fg text} key in the Node Startup-Screen of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "REMOTELGN" "Main Window: Remote Login Button"

                          @{u}REMOTE LOGIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this Button if you want to let a user come onto your BBS on the same
 line that you are currently talking to him on (via voice). To use this,
 click once on this button, then click on the node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node
 the user should login (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = nodenr. you wish). At the same time the user
 should enter @{b}ATD@{ub} in his Terminal to force the modem to connect. Also you
 must hang up your telephone to establish the connection.

This function is equal to the @{fg shine}<F3>@{fg text} key in the Node Startup-Screen of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "INITMODEM" "Main Window: Init Modem Button"

                           @{u}INIT MODEM BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to re-initialize your modems. Click once on this button
 and then on the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you wish to re-initialize
 (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = nodenr. you wish). The Server uses the Initialization Commands
 specified in the @{fg fill}SystemEditor/Node Settings@{fg text} for the according node.

 This function is equal to the @{fg shine}<F8>@{fg text} key in the Node Startup-Screen of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SYSFASTLGN" "Main Window: Sysop Fast Login"

                          @{u}SYSOP FAST LOGIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button lets you login as SysOp, but in difference to the normal 
 @{"SysOp Login" link "SYSOPLOGIN" 0} Procedure, all Textfiles are skipped and no Message/File 
 Scanning will be performed. The rest of this Logon type is the same as
 described in the SysOp Login Procedure.
 After pressing this button select the node you wish to login as SysOp.
 Click on the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = nodenr. you wish) and FAME starts
 the Login procedure. It's not necessary to have the node screen open, 
 the login will be done in any case.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F1@{fg text}> key in the Node Startup-Screen
 of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "LOCFASTLGN" "Main Window: Local Fast Login Button"

                         @{u}LOCAL FAST LOGIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button allows you to login local under a specific Username, but in
 difference to the normal @{"Local Login" link "LOCALLOGIN" 0} procedure all Textfiles and the
 File/Message Scanning are disabled. The rest of this login procedure is
 the same as the Local Login.
 After pressing this button, click on the node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you
 wish to login (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = the nodenr. you wish).

 The fact that you now have to enter the username that you wish to login as
 means that you need to open the node screen to type the details into.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F2@{fg text}> key in the Node Startup-Screen
 of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "REMFASTLGN" "Main Window: Remote Fast Login Button"

                         @{u}REMOTE FAST LOGIN BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this Button if you want to let a user come onto your BBS on the same
 line you are currently talking to him on (e.g. via voice). To use this,
 click once on this button, then click on the node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node
 the user should login (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = nodenr. you wish). At the same time the user
 should enter @{b}ATD@{ub} in his Terminal to force the modem to connect. Also you
 must hang up your telephone to establish the connection.

 In difference to the normal @{"Remote Login" link "REMOTELGN" 0} procedure, all textfiles and
 the File/Message scanning are disabled.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F3@{fg text}> key in the Node Startup-Screen
 of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "NODE_CHAT" "Main Window: Node Chat Button"

                            @{u}NODE CHAT BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to go to the SysOp chat with one of your online users. You
 have to click first on this button, then select the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the
 node you want to go to SysOp chat (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish). FAME will then
 (if needed) open the Nodescreen and start the SysOp-Chat.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}F1@{fg text}> key inside the Nodescreen @{b}if a user@{ub} 
 @{b}is currently online on this node@{ub}.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "INFO_CYCLE" "Main Window: List of last UL/DL/Callers   "

               @{u}CYCLE-GADGET: LAST CALLERS/UPLOADS/DOWNLOADS@{uu}

 This Gadget is used to cycle between the list of the @{b}last ten callers@{ub}, the
 @{b}last ten uploads@{ub} (filenames) or the @{b}last ten downloads@{ub} (filenames). This is
 useful to have a quick overview what recently happend on your BBS.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "BANKCYCLE" "Main Window: Cycle the Button-Banks"

               @{u}CYCLE-GADGET: SYSTEM/USER-BUTTON SWITCH@{uu}

 Use this Cycle-Gadget to switch between the @{b}System Button@{ub} and @{b}Userbutton@{ub}
 banks one and two. The Userbutton banks are freely configurable in the 
 @{"SystemEditor" link "SystemEditor.guide/Main"} of FAME. Look also in Chapter @{"Configuration of the Buttons" link "CONFIGURATION" 0}
 for further information how to install your own buttons.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "EXIT_NODE" "Main Window: Exit Node Button"

                            @{u}EXIT NODE BUTTON:@{uu}

 This Button allows you to ShutDown already started nodes. To use this,
 click once on this button then choose the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you
 want to shutdown (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish). FAME will then ShutDown the
 choosen node. It can be restarted by pressing once on the Node button.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}F9@{fg text}> key of the Node-Startup screen of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ICNFY_NODE" "Main Window: Iconify Node Button"

                           @{u}ICONIFY NODE BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this Button to iconify node screen(s). Click once on this button,
 then choose the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the Node you want to iconify it's screen
 (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish). FAME will then iconify the Nodescreen if it's
 currently open.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F10@{fg text}> or <@{fg shine}RAMIGA+I@{fg text}> key shortcuts in
 the FAME node Await Logon screen.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "DROP_USER" "Main Window: Drop User Button"

                           @{u}DROP USER BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to drop the carrier on a currently online user. Click once
 on this button, then choose the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you want
 to drop the carrier of the user (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish). FAME will then 
 drop the user's carrier and re-initialize after the logoff batches where
 executed.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}F10@{fg text}> key in the FAME node screen (@{b}but only@{ub}
 @{b}if a user is currently online!@{ub}).

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "N#_OFFHOOK" "Main Window: Node OffHook Button"

                           @{u}NODE OFFHOOK BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to @{b}shutdown@{ub} and @{b}offhook@{ub} specific nodes. In difference to
 the @{"Exit Node" link "EXIT_NODE" 0} button the node you have choosen will be made offhook, which
 means the line will be busy to anyone that tries to call this node.

 To use this, click once on this button, then choose the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button
 of the node you want to make shutdown/offhook (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish).
 FAME will then shutdown the node and also make it offhook (busy).

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}F10@{fg text}> key of the Node-Startup screen if no
 user is online, and the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F10@{fg text}> key if a user is currently online.
 See documentation of the @{i}FAME Nodescreen GUI@{ui} for further informations about
 all supported function keys.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "System_Ed" "Main Window: System Editor Button"

                          @{u}SYSTEM-EDITOR BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button starts the System-Editor of FAME. To let this work, you have
 to set the correct path to the System-Editor in the @{fg fill}System-Editor@{fg text} settings
 under @{fg fill}FAME Modules@{fg text}.

 The System-Editor is used whenever you need to change something in the
 configuration of FAME. A complete description of the System-Editor can be
 found in the @{i}System-Editor documentation@{ui} supplied with FAME.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F5@{fg text}> key in the node-startup screen of
 FAME. Also you are able to access the System-Editor when pressing the @{b}HELP@{ub}
 key on an activated FAME Nodescreen. See @{i}Nodescreen GUI documentation@{ui} for
 further informations about all available keycommands.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "USER_EDIT" "Main Window: User Editor Button"

                            @{u}USER-EDITOR BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to start the external User-Editor supplied with FAME. You
 have to set the correct path to the User-Editor in the @{fg fill}System-Editor@{fg text} under
 @{fg fill}FAME Modules@{fg text} to let this button work.

 The external User-Editor can be used to change datas of specific users 
 without using the internal Usereditor which requires a node to be started.

 See also the @{"Node-specific calls" link "NODE_USEREDIT" 0} for the User-Editor to get more detailed
 informations.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}SHIFT+F6@{fg text}> key in the node-startup screen of
 FAME. Also you are able to access the User-Editor when pressing the @{b}HELP@{ub}
 key on an activated FAME Nodescreen. See @{i}Nodescreen GUI documentation@{ui} for
 further informations about all available keycommands.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "N#_RESERVE" "Main Window: Reserve Node Button"

                           @{u}NODE RESERVE BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to reserve a node for a specific user. To use this, click
 once on this button and then choose the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node
 you want to reserve (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish). FAME will then open the
 choosen nodescreen and you will now asked for the Username to reserve
 the node for. If you press @{b}ENTER@{ub} without entering a name, the reserving
 will be aborted, otherwise the Node will now be reserved for the user
 you have entered.

 This function is equal to the <@{fg shine}F4@{fg text}> key in the Node-Startup screen of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "QUIET_NODE" "Main Window: Quiet Node Button"

                            @{u}QUIET NODE BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to make a user "@{b}hidden@{ub}" for other users. Click once on
 this button, then select the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the user's node you want to
 make hidden (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish).

 This function is equal to the '@{fg shine}Q@{fg text}' command on the BBS-Prompt. See the
 @{"MainPart" link "MainPart.guide/Main"} @{i}documentation@{ui} for detailed informations about all supported
 commands of FAME.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "SPY_NODE" "Main Window: Spy Node Button"

                            @{u}SPY NODE BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button allows you to "@{b}spy@{ub}" on a specific node, which means that you
 could view all actions by the online user without having to open the
 node screen first. To use this, click once on this button, then select
 the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you want to spy (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish).
 FAME will then open a window on your Workbench screen and show all user
 actions in this window.

 You can configure the window in the @{fg fill}System-Editor@{fg text} under @{fg fill}System Datas/@{fg text}
 @{fg fill}More System Datas@{fg text}. Here you can define @{b}how many lines@{ub} the window should
 display and if @{b}your keyinputs@{ub} should @{b}passed through the node@{ub} or if all
 @{b}inputs inside the Spy window are disabled@{ub}. Look in the @{i}System-Editor@{ui}
 @{i}documentation@{ui} for further informations about these settings.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "CONF_NODE" "Main Window: Config Node Button"

                         @{u}CONFIGURE NODE BUTTON:@{uu}

 This button will be used to configure specific node settings. Click once
 on this button, then choose the Node @{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} button of the node you want to
 configure (@{fg fill}<x>@{fg text} = Nodenr. you wish). 

   <@{fg shine}THIS FUNCTION IS CURRENTLY UNDER DEVELOPMENT AND IS NOT 100% WORKING !@{fg text}>

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "ALLICONIFY" "Main Window: All Iconify Button"

                          @{u}ALL ICONIFY BUTTON:@{uu}

 Use this button to iconify all currently open node screens. Useful if you
 have chatted with many users on different nodes and forgot to close all
 screens after the chats. A single click on this button will do this for
 you.

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

@node "UNUSED" "Main Window: Unused Buttons"

     < @{fg shine}THESE BUTTONS ARE CURRENTLY EMPTY. ANY SUGGESTIONS FOR THEM ? :)@{fg text} >

@endnode

@REM==============================================================================

